<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="87" type="differential diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Differential diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="87">
Collecting the tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lopatin" authorityYear="1961" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="tribe" tribe="Sogdini">Sogdini</taxonomicName>
is generally not easy in Japan and identified Japanese specimens of the tribe are very small in quantity. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hoshina" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Triarthron" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Triarthron itoi" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="itoi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Triarthron itoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hoshina, sp. nov. is described based on only one specimen; therefore, the degree of individual variation cannot be determined in this species. However, I found some morphological features on that specimen that are clearly different from two known species of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Triarthron" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Triarthron" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Triarthron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and recognize it as a new member of the genus. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hoshina" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Triarthron" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Triarthron itoi" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="itoi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Triarthron itoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. maerkelii" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="maerkelii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">T. maerkelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Märkel">Maerkel</normalizedToken>
, 1840 by the following features: it has a large body whose length is 4.8 mm, mesofemur with relatively large teeth at the dorsal lamina of the posterior margin (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 2–7" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 2 - 7. Triarthron itoi Hoshina, sp. nov. (2 - 5). 2 Body 3 right antennomere, dorsal view 4 left mesofemur, ventral view 5 left metafemur, ventral view. T. maerkelii Maerkel (6, 7). 6 Left mesofemur, ventral view 7 left metafemur, ventral view. Scale bar: A: 1 mm (2), B: 0.2 mm (3), C, D: 0.5 mm (4 - 7)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.938.51614.figures2-7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/418209" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">4</figureCitation>
), metafemur strongly expanded anteriorly at about half of the antero-apical margin (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 2–7" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 2 - 7. Triarthron itoi Hoshina, sp. nov. (2 - 5). 2 Body 3 right antennomere, dorsal view 4 left mesofemur, ventral view 5 left metafemur, ventral view. T. maerkelii Maerkel (6, 7). 6 Left mesofemur, ventral view 7 left metafemur, ventral view. Scale bar: A: 1 mm (2), B: 0.2 mm (3), C, D: 0.5 mm (4 - 7)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.938.51614.figures2-7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/418209" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">5</figureCitation>
), and median lobe of aedeagus weakly and simply curved at lateral margins in dorsal view (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 8–10" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 8 - 10. Triarthron itoi Hoshina sp. nov. (8, 9). 8 Aedeagus, dorsal view 9 ditto, lateral view. T. maerkelii Maerkel (10) aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bar: 0.5 mm (8 - 10)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.938.51614.figures8-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/418210" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">8</figureCitation>
). In contrast, 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. maerkelii" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="maerkelii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">T. maerkelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in the following ways: it has a relatively small body whose length is 2.5-3.8 mm (
<bibRefCitation author="Daffner, H" journalOrPublisher="Folia Entomologica Hungarica" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="9 - 163" refId="B2" refString="Daffner, H, 1983. Revision der palaerktischen Arten der Tribus Leiodini Leach (Coleoptera, Leiodidae). Folia Entomologica Hungarica 44: 9 - 163" title="Revision der palaerktischen Arten der Tribus Leiodini Leach (Coleoptera, Leiodidae)." volume="44" year="1983">Daffner 1983</bibRefCitation>
), mesofemur with teeth less-visible because of being hidden by ventral side of mesofemur (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 2–7" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 2 - 7. Triarthron itoi Hoshina, sp. nov. (2 - 5). 2 Body 3 right antennomere, dorsal view 4 left mesofemur, ventral view 5 left metafemur, ventral view. T. maerkelii Maerkel (6, 7). 6 Left mesofemur, ventral view 7 left metafemur, ventral view. Scale bar: A: 1 mm (2), B: 0.2 mm (3), C, D: 0.5 mm (4 - 7)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.938.51614.figures2-7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/418209" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">6</figureCitation>
), metafemur relatively weakly expanded anteriorly at about half of antero-apical margin (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 2–7" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 2 - 7. Triarthron itoi Hoshina, sp. nov. (2 - 5). 2 Body 3 right antennomere, dorsal view 4 left mesofemur, ventral view 5 left metafemur, ventral view. T. maerkelii Maerkel (6, 7). 6 Left mesofemur, ventral view 7 left metafemur, ventral view. Scale bar: A: 1 mm (2), B: 0.2 mm (3), C, D: 0.5 mm (4 - 7)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.938.51614.figures2-7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/418209" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">7</figureCitation>
), and median lobe sharply narrowed from about apical 2/5 towards apex (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 8–10" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 8 - 10. Triarthron itoi Hoshina sp. nov. (8, 9). 8 Aedeagus, dorsal view 9 ditto, lateral view. T. maerkelii Maerkel (10) aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bar: 0.5 mm (8 - 10)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.938.51614.figures8-10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/418210" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">10</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
