<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="87">
Moreover, 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. itoi" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="itoi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">T. itoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. can be separated from 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. lecontei" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="lecontei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">T. lecontei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Horn, 1868 by having both mandibles sharply curved inwardly at about apical 1/4 and lacking large teeth at internal margins, and metafemur strongly expanded at the anterior margin (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 2–7" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 2 - 7. Triarthron itoi Hoshina, sp. nov. (2 - 5). 2 Body 3 right antennomere, dorsal view 4 left mesofemur, ventral view 5 left metafemur, ventral view. T. maerkelii Maerkel (6, 7). 6 Left mesofemur, ventral view 7 left metafemur, ventral view. Scale bar: A: 1 mm (2), B: 0.2 mm (3), C, D: 0.5 mm (4 - 7)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.938.51614.figures2-7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/418209" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">5</figureCitation>
). In contrast, 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. lecontei" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="lecontei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">T. lecontei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has both mandibles relatively weakly curved inwardly at internal margins, right one with an elongated sub-apical tooth, and metafemur almost straight at the anterior margin (
<bibRefCitation author="Hatch, MH" journalOrPublisher="University of Washington Press, Seattle, Washington" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" refId="B3" refString="Hatch, MH, 1957. The beetles of the Pacific Northwest. Part II: Staphyliniformia. University of Washington Publications in Biology 16. University of Washington Press, Seattle, Washington" title="The beetles of the Pacific Northwest. Part II: Staphyliniformia. University of Washington Publications in Biology 16." year="1957">Hatch 1957</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2102.1.1" author="Peck, SB" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="1 - 74" refId="B16" refString="Peck, SB, Cook, J, 2009. Review of the Sogdini of North and Central America (Coleoptera: Leiodidae: Leiodinae) with descriptions of fourteen new species and three new genera. Zootaxa 2102: 1 - 74, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2102.1.1" title="Review of the Sogdini of North and Central America (Coleoptera: Leiodidae: Leiodinae) with descriptions of fourteen new species and three new genera." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2102.1.1" volume="2102" year="2009">Peck and Cook 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
